	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/styles/main.css">
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/styles/care.css">
	<title>Cat Care</title>
</head>
<body onload="localTime()">
	<div id="page">
		<!-- header -->
		<%- include('common/header.ejs') %>
		
		<!-- side menu -->
		<%- include('common/navbar.ejs') %>
		
		<!-- main content -->
		<main>
			<h3 class="heading-title">Cat Care</h3>
			<div class="parent">
				<div class="child-2">
					<article>
						<h3>Nutrition</h3>
						<p>
							&ndash; Provide a balanced diet rich in protein, essential fatty acids, vitamins, and minerals. <br>
							&ndash; Choose high-quality cat food formulated for their life stage (kitten, adult, senior). <br>
							&ndash; Ensure access to fresh water at all times. <br>
							&ndash; Avoid feeding toxic foods like chocolate, onions, garlic, and grapes.
						</p>
					</article>
					<article>
						<h3>Shelter</h3>
						<p>
							&ndash; Provide a safe, warm, and comfortable indoor environment. <br>
							&ndash; Offer a cozy bed or resting area. <br>
							&ndash; Create vertical spaces like cat trees for climbing and perching. <br>
							&ndash; Provide scratching posts to satisfy their natural urge to scratch.
						</p>
					</article>
					<article>
						<h3>Health Care</h3>
						<p>
							&ndash; Schedule regular veterinary check-ups for vaccinations, deworming, and overall health assessment. <br>
							&ndash; Spay or neuter your cat to prevent unwanted pregnancies and health issues. <br>
							&ndash; Keep up with flea and tick prevention treatments. <br>
							&ndash; Monitor their dental health and brush their teeth regularly. <br>
							&ndash; Be aware of signs of illness and seek prompt veterinary care if needed.
						</p>
					</article>
					<article>
						<h3>Mental Stimulation</h3>
						<p>
							&ndash; Provide toys that encourage physical activity and mental stimulation. <br>
							&ndash; Rotate toys regularly to prevent boredom. <br>
							&ndash; Spend quality time playing and interacting with your cat. <br>
							&ndash; Consider puzzle feeders or food-dispensing toys to keep them mentally engaged.
						</p>
					</article>
				</div>
				<article>
					<h3>Litter Box Care</h3>
					<p>
						&ndash; Provide a clean litter box in a quiet, easily accessible location. <br>
						&ndash; Scoop the litter box daily and change the litter completely every 1-2 weeks. <br>
						&ndash; Use unscented, clumping litter that your cat prefers. <br>
						&ndash; Ensure multiple litter boxes in multi-cat households.
					</p>
				</article>
			</div>
		</main>
		
		<!-- footer -->
		<%- include('common/footer.ejs') %>
	</div>
	<script src="/scripts/index.js"></script>
</body>
</html>